               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000048l2-1" xml:lang="en"> The great gate (damen 大門) leading into the complex was likely added when the shrine was rebuilt in the second year of the Qianlong period (1737). A single bay wide with a gable roof. Liu Dapeng described it as a <term ref="/keyword/k000116">fang 坊</term> gateway (Liu 1986, 32-33). Also called a <term ref="/keyword/k000212">paifang 牌坊</term> (Liu 2016. 157), this is an architectural form which facilitates the installation of formal name-plaques pai 牌.</p>
               </desc>
